## 05 Strategy & Positioning

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Key Message | Ascorbyl Glucoside Solution 12%. Stable, water-soluble Vitamin C derivative. No fragrance. No unnecessary ingredients. Honest price. |
| Competitive Differentiator | Clinical concentration at a fraction of luxury brand pricing. Ascorbyl Glucoside is more stable and less irritating than L-Ascorbic Acid. INCI-transparent. No proprietary blends, no hidden markup. |
| Brand Voice | **DO:** clinical, honest, ingredient-specific, no-nonsense, direct. **DON'T:** aspirational language, vague glow claims, luxury signalling, celebrity talent, emotional manipulation. |
| Brand Guardrails | Logo top-left end card. Brand color: black `#000000`, white background. Show real skin — no retouching, no filters. Legal: results disclaimer required for any efficacy claim. |

---

## 06 Tone & Creative Direction

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Tone / Vibe | Clinical, honest, minimal. The Ordinary's brand voice is anti-hype — let the ingredient data speak. No warmth performance, just clarity. |
| Visual References | Macro liquid texture, dropper bottle with clear amber formula, clean white surfaces, clinical lighting. Ref: The Ordinary's own product photography — stark, honest, ingredient-forward. No warmth filters, no lifestyle set dressing. |
| Talent / Casting | Diverse adults 22–40, all skin tones and types. Real skin texture — visible pores, natural variation. No makeup, no filters. Must look like the actual customer, not a skincare model. |
| Music & Sound | 50–65 BPM, minimal ambient, single piano motif, no strings, no percussion. Clinical and precise. Reference: Nils Frahm Spaces — silence is part of the composition. |
| Pacing | Extremely slow and deliberate. Macro textures held 4s+. S3: full 8-second static hold on bottle. No cuts that feel rushed. Silence and stillness are intentional brand signals. |
| Supers / Text on Screen | S3 at 0:15: `Ascorbyl Glucoside 12%` — black Arial Bold 48pt on white, hold 4s. End Card: `Scan to shop` + `theordinary.com/ctv` + QR + code `SPRING20`. |

